{"id":1153,"date":"2022-02-12T19:26:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-12T19:26:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1153"},"modified":"2022-03-17T11:54:44","modified_gmt":"2022-03-17T11:54:44","slug":"diagnose-and-correct-file-permission-problems","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1153","title":{"rendered":"Diagnose and correct file permission problems"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>To gain some general knowledge about the file permissions, you should first read <a href=\"https:\/\/access.redhat.com\/documentation\/en-us\/red_hat_enterprise_linux\/8\/html\/configuring_basic_system_settings\/assembly_managing-file-permissions_configuring-basic-system-settings\">this<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As the name suggest, the whole topic is about understanding the permissions and changing something if it&#8217;s wrongly configured.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Let&#8217;s point out few important things that you probably know about<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>In the Linux OS to determine which permissions a user has the Linux uses something called ownership<\/li><li>Every file has a user-owner and group owner<\/li><li>Permissions work slightly different on files and directories<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"466\" height=\"158\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?resize=466%2C158&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1456\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?w=466&amp;ssl=1 466w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?resize=300%2C102&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-59.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 466px) 100vw, 466px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>To display files permissions and ownership we use &#8220;<strong>ls -l&#8221; <\/strong>command<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"575\" height=\"81\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?resize=575%2C81&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1156\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?w=575&amp;ssl=1 575w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?resize=300%2C42&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-99.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 575px) 100vw, 575px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>To change these permissions, we use <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=729\">chmod <\/a><\/strong>command<\/li><li>To change the ownership of the user owner or group owner, we use <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=729\">chown<\/a><\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"596\" height=\"151\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?resize=596%2C151&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1157\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?w=596&amp;ssl=1 596w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?resize=300%2C76&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?resize=24%2C6&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?resize=36%2C9&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-100.png?resize=48%2C12&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Besides read, write and execute we know and use <a href=\"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1100\">SUID<\/a>, SGID, Sticky bit<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"119\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=640%2C119&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1457\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?w=826&amp;ssl=1 826w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=300%2C56&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=768%2C142&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/image-60.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>We apply these special permissions with either using numbers or letters<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"266\" height=\"264\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?resize=266%2C264&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1160\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?w=266&amp;ssl=1 266w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?resize=24%2C24&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?resize=36%2C36&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-103.png?resize=48%2C48&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 266px) 100vw, 266px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Look for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.redhat.com\/sysadmin\/linux-access-control-lists\">ACLs<\/a> as well as permissions on the files and directories<\/li><li>ACLs don&#8217;t show up with <strong>ls -l<\/strong>, you need to use <strong>getfacl<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"284\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?resize=640%2C284&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1161\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?w=641&amp;ssl=1 641w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?resize=300%2C133&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-104.png?resize=48%2C21&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I think these are all the most important ones, I&#8217;m sure there are plenty more, but the main key is to know what everything does. How to create and remove new ones and try it out a lot inside your own VM.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To gain some general knowledge about the file permissions, you should first read this. As [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1067,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[414,408,406,410,407,409,220,412,413,411],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/rhsa-Create-and-configure-file-systems.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1153"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=1153"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1153\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1458,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1153\/revisions\/1458"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/1067"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner